{
  "stem": "12491.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was another one was a-- where they used to make cables and wires.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were three outside camps, which eventually were-- well, they were all under jurisdiction of Plaszow and of it's commandant.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At any rate, we all three got on the list.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "To make this story short, unfortunately, people who had the money paid enough money that my sister my brother were taken off the list, and I was-- I remained.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This is why I wound up at Schindler's, and they did not.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were taken-- sometime in October my sister was taken to Stutthof, where she, unfortunately, was killed, and my brother was taken to Gusen, in Austria, where he, unfortunately, was killed.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I didn't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I wasn't privileged enough to know what is happening behind the scenes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What I heard later-- but this would be more rumors or hearsay than-- than-- than real knowledge-- that some of that money went to Schindler.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some of that money and the diamonds went to the-- the Jewish people who were in charge of preparing the list for Schindler.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of them, possibly still alive, is, I think, in Argentina.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I know that through the information received through the New Cracow Friendship Society of-- in New York, of which I am a member.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now to return to the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] time, which we mentioned, that the boy was hidden in the latrine.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This happened during May of 1943, when the Germans have decided that the concentration camp Plaszow will not have any children.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they assembled all the children and evacuated them, but few of them managed to escape and hide within the camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
